agnew would attack his adversaries with relish , hurling unusual , often alliterative epithets , some of which were coined by white house speechwriters william safire and pat buchanan , including " pusillanimous pussyfooters , " " nattering nabobs of negativism " ( written by safire ) and " hopeless , hysterical hypochondriacs of history . " in a speech denouncing the moratorium to end the war in vietnam , he characterized the war 's opponents as " an effete corps of impudent snobs who characterize themselves as intellectuals . "

